reviews.text: This experience was horrible being my first time here! They're over crowded and they need better chefs. I was told I couldn't get my money back by the manager with the dentures because I was there for two hours even though I didn't eat. It was so ghetto....ugh and dirty. Food was uncooked and everything. Save your money and time.

Came here for Thanksgiving and honestly had low expectations.  These guys blew me away. My server was Darryl and he was top notch. The ham was so succulent you could cut it with a fork. The rolls were their usual to die for yumminess. I was seriously impressed and it really made my Thanksgiving to be surrounded by such awesome people and food.

Worst experience than any other.
People is nice but management is terrible. No plates available, you have to chase people around to get service. cross contamination everywhere, they use gloves but they touch money, your plate and everything with the same one. “Rambo” is around giving orders like is the military.
Save your money and have a better experience going to Mc donalds

Golden Corral Buffet was the perfect place to get the main part of my Christmas meal.  I purchased turkey breast and dressing.  The turkey was fresh, moist and seasoned perfectly.  It was also carved into slices which was less work for me. The dressing was savory and a delight. I'm giving a special shout out to the manager Mr. Demetrius who is always professional, customer friendly, and makes sure everything runs smoothly.

I love buffets. And I guess my belly reflects it. Most of the food was great! The server, Roxanne,  was great! Ask for her section. They also had plastic gloves and hand sanitizer available. I hadn't been there in a while.  I'll be returning soon.

Thank you to the staff at Chuck E. Cheese Largo for giving our daughter a memorable 6th birthday party. The children enjoyed playing games, eating the delicious pizza and seeing Chuck E. We also loved that Chuck E danced with the children and allowed everyone to take pictures with him. Our event was on Sunday from 1:30-3:30pm so there wasn’t a crowd. Special thanks to our server ,Tynisha, and rest of the staff for going above and beyond for our event. We will definitely be back!

I celebrated my son’s birthday this past weekend, and the service was fantastic. Parties are typically chaotic, but the Manager and Dezmond made my experience a breeze. They made sure that we could enjoy the party while they took care of the party, food, and check-up on the parents and guests throughout the party. I believe the placement of seating was thought out correctly to accompany our big party. Thank you for helping us celebrate our son's birthday and for the excellent service provided.

The food was average and what I would expect for a Chuck e Cheese. The service was higher quality than I have seen at other Chuck e Cheese establishments with the high number of parties going on simultaneously. The atmosphere was tolerable, but not one that I would want to regularly frequent with my child, largely due to the people hanging out outside, but in close proximity to the Chuck e Cheese (cursing, smoking, etc.)

Crazy food prices and the food takes forever to come out and you have to wait in a long line to recieve it. Plus one of the two pizzas I ordered for my child's birthday party was complete cold and nasty to the point where the cheese had hardend up.
Very friendly staff that does their best to keep everything working! Our kids had fun, and so did all of the other happy families!

A friend recommended me that I try this place. Sit down dining is not available, take out only. There is a line inside, but it moves quickly. They food is laid out behind the counter, and you can see what's available. It set up like a moving line. If you want something on the menu that's not currently there, you will have to wait 20-30. minutes for them to make it. The baby back ribs for example were not available at the time. The Smoothered Pork Chops are a good choice. Make sure you ask for gravy on the side, because they will drown the gravy, and it will be all over in your carton. Make sure they give it to you because they almost forgot. The food was good. I just have this thing about food being on the menu, and it's not available. I asked for three different desserts, and they were not available. So why even have it on the menu then? Other than that, the food was very good, and seasoned well.

Great ambience. Plenty of food selections and they give you huge portions. I had BBQ chicken,  yams, collard greens, corn bread, and strawberry cake.  The food was  delicious. The strawberry cake however was a little on the dry side might have just been a little old. It had strawberry filling in the center and that was tasty. Staff was friendly. It was nice, warm, and energetic! Great for the cold snowy day I went!

This was our first time eating here and when I tell you the ambiance and service and food was amazing. I also got to me the owner and she’s delightful. I will be back when visiting or possibly doing my externship here to finish out school. Thank you much Carolina Kitchen for the great experience!

Drove from Laurel to Largo to purchase fried chicken, cabbage, collard greens, potato salad and a slice of lemon cake. Chicken was fried a little too hard for my liking, potatoes in the potato salad were more like mashed potatoes; collard greens had too many stems and the flavor was off; lemon cake was wet not moist. Guessing there’s new cooks in the kitchen and they’re not following recipes. This is my first time since they reopened.

The service here sucks. The food was cold and there was a line worker visibly intoxicated and he was dropping food allover the counter, couldn't tell which part of the chicken was white or dark meat and the list goes on. The food is too expensive to be served cold or having incompetent worker's.
The manager needs to take some lessons on customer service as well.  It's a shame that the employees don't care enough to do great work.

I went Friday around 2:30. I was surprised how so busy it was but they have a lunch menu until 3. Anyway we were told the wait would be 45 minutes. You leave your number and they text you when they are ready to seat you. The text  said 15 to 30 minutes. So we waited outside, not long at all. We were seated, the waitress was nice and friendly. The appetizers and food were great. Nice atmosphere. No problems going back smiley face.

The chicken thigh appetizer was the bomb, That skin was so crispy! The drinks were pretty good too. I used to hate this place because it was gross, haven't been here in YEARS but now things seem a little better. Might even go back. But I came in with a wedding party and they accommodated us. They don't split checks.

Service was amazingly great, food was as well but the spinach dip wasn’t too good.! This is a nice restaurant with good vibes. I definitely will be going again and recommend others to try it out.. the dishes in the pictures are the broiled seafood platter, the shrimp and chicken pasta, and crab meat egg rolls! Didn’t get a picture of the drinks but the drinks are good tasting and strong..!

Definitely recommend trying this place at least once. You won't be disappointed! I had the salmon and grits and it was out of this world. Never had anything like it. The vibe. The service. Everything was on point.

The place is cool! I like the ambiance. I ordered the French toast. At first glance it looked like chicken, but the French toast was deep fried. It had caramel sauce and it tasted good. Unfortunately, I wasn't offered syrup. I would go back and try something else.

I'm not going to lie this was the best IHOP experience I ever had . From the time we stepped in the door we was greeted very well. Serves from the manager was amazing they made sure we was comfortable and got our orders and food in a timely manner and even the food looked and taste amazing I don't want to go to no other IHOP if there not like this one they even made the kids smile and gave them dollars that later because they was so happy left as extra tips for the waitress

We ordered to go. I got a French toast combo. I got one slice of French toast and a table spoon of eggs. I typically don't come to this one, but it was on the way home. They had nice service and the wait was reasonable, but these portion sizes are disappointing.
Had a pleasant time at the IHOP not too crowded on a Friday evening service was quick and the food was delicious also the prices were very afford

Sirloin Tips,  potatoes,  eggs and pancakes.  The first meal was burnt.  We sent them back and the second meal was awesome.  Our server was awesome as well.  I'm so upset I forgot his name,  it had a latin vibe to it.  Anyway he was on point.  One of the best experiences.

Ordered a full order of biscuits and gravy to go.  This little container had 2  biscuits and 2 condiment size containers of the worse gravy I have had in my life. Definitely not worth the wait or the price!!!! I should have just went to McDonald's or anywhere else.   Do not get the biscuits and gravy.

name: Subway
vicinity: 978 Largo Center Drive Unit #29, Upper Marlboro

reviews.text:
It’s super cool you get to build-your-own sandwiches but then the staff need to be a little bit more patient with first time customers like myself that have little or no knowledge about the menu options. Nonetheless, the footlong sub sandwich paired with simple fresh orange juice and lays baked potato chips on the side is Delectable, yum!
First time here and maybe I might be back again.......
Good Food ✅
Healthy Options✅
Casual Dining ✅
♿️Wheelchair Accessible Entrance✅
♿️Wheel Chair Accessible Parking Lot✅
🅿️ Adequate Parking Space ✅
♿️Wheel Chair Accessible Restroom 🚻

I know if send this picture to the corporate office they will not be happy.
1st let me start with how worker’s/Owners don’t care every time you walk in they talk on the phone even while they making the order some times you will repeat what you said more than one time, not to mention last time when I finished my order he said they don’t have more bags and he gave a used bag.
I asked for a sauce and he give me that in a cup 🤨!

I have come to this location many times but yesterday will most likely be my last time. The individual who made my sandwich was on the phone while taking my order, rude to me when i corrected him about my order, was rude through the whole process and then double charged me. Got mad when i approached him about being double charged and decided to get loud and get his colleague involved. He refused to give me his manager's information when i asked. His colleague agreed with me and told him he was wrong and to fix it. I only gave a star so i could leave this review.

New weekend staff needed at this location!!!! What happened to the previous staff? The black guy who worked this afternoon,  March 20th 2022 was horrible.  You cannot catch an attitude for not hearing my order while TALKING ON YOUR PHONE!!! PICK A STRUGGLE!!! IT'S NOT THE FIRST TIME!! UNPROFESSIONAL.

Everytime i go in this place There's a old short spanish guy that's just absolutely ignorant and rude for no reason!! I always go and get my mother's sandwiches from the other surrounding subway's but this one was closer for where she is. If he owns the store that's horrible but i highly doubt he's the owner and the owner needs to teach him better manners!!
He is just plain evil i will never come back in there again, God Rest my friends soul cause he's the reason he never went there and i see why. Smh

Redevelopment has reached Largo/Landover in the area where The Golden Corral and Magic Johnson AMC Theatres is located; I hadn't been to that Friday's over there in years prior to the Pandemic and after. I decided to have a day out with my children and grandchild , so we all agreed to eat at Friday's then catch the movie NOPE at The Magic Johnson Theater. I was not disappointed. We had a blast, it was my grandson's second outing since the world started to move again. I ordered The Bucket of Bones which consists of chicken and ribs with fries based with the famous Jack Daniel's Whiskey sauce, my oldest daughter ordered the Chicken Parmesan, my grandbaby had mashed potatoes and broccoli and my baby ordered almost everything. OMG!! I thought that Friday's had gone down , the service was superb. The atmosphere was cozy and laid back and it helps that PG County's finest stay posted to keep unwanted drama away. We had a blast!!

Disappointed in Rudy the Manager for not being willing to accommodate us with a to go cup.  He thought that we should drink all drinks inside.  I asked him is that because of the location where he is located for the shortage in not ordering enough cups. I find that to be very disappointing and disturbing.  He told me I could pay $2 for a cup when I just paid $4 for a drink—knowing full well foam Cup don’t cost that much. He was not willing to Compromise and was comfortable with me leaving this review about him as he Scrugged his shoulders and walked away.  We have to do better people—my ask was not that much.  Our waitress was much better than him
And that is what you call poor leadership:(

If I could give this place zero stars I would!! Horrible from the second we walked in. There are signs all over the front entrance stating that they are not responsible for stolen or left items - very strange but after reading reviews, it appears that there has been several incidents. Hostess finally sat the 4 of us down after 10 minutes of just standing there talking to a co-worker. The table we were sat at was not very clean and still sticky. It took the waitress 15 minutes to come over and introduce herself and take our drink order. After bringing our drinks, she disappeared. After 20 minutes we could see her walking around the restaurant and she would pass our table saying she would be right back - which didn't happen. After another 15 minutes, she finally reappeared and we got her attention just for her to tell us she would be right back to get our order. At this point, we told her to just bring us our check for the drinks and we left. Not once did she apologize, the bill was $11 so we have her a $20 and she got an attitude when we said we wanted our change! I definitely do not recommend this TGI Fridays at all!! Horrible staff, dirty restaurant and just plain POOR customer service.

Terri’s was an excellent host and bartender! She was attentive and also was on point with the drinks. Yes the bar was packed but she ensured she made sure I was happy with what was in my cup as well as what was in my plate! I will be back!

I ordered take out. I got a coupon for a free dessert from my email.. I used it... big mistake. FYI don't use their "free coupons" you will get a stale brownie. It was nasty. I wished I had just paid for my dessert so I might have gotten a good one. Also the burgers were soggy and fries were under cooked. Not coming back. I did like this place and did orfer often but not going to spend the money not sure if I'm going to get a decent meal.

So, the service could use a bit of TLC from management; the bartender tended to our needs, (I had to get accustomed to his personality) but he did not have good support from the other staff. (Others socializing and not being aware of the needs of customers) The food was subpar (mashed potatoes looked and tasted old and zucchini lacked flavor) but the steak was very tender and flavorful. I do plan on giving them another chance since the location is close, but just 1 more chance lol. Stay safe ✌🏿

On a work trip, a coworker and I stopped by Ruby Tuesday’s for what we thought would be a nice and quick dinner. We were in for a surprise.

Upon entering a fairly empty restaurant we asked to be seated at a table with chairs rather than a booth. We were seated on one side of the restaurant literally by ourselves. Maybe their weren’t tables on the other side. This wouldn’t have been an issue if we weren’t greeted by any wait staff. After about 15 mins we eventually asked the host to find our server.

After going to look he came back and graciously took our drink order. About 5 minutes later our drinks were brought out by our actual waitress who was otherwise very pleasant.

Food took a long time to come out and we overheard the host state that there was a 40 min wait to eat. The restaurant couldn’t have been more than 15% -20% full so this was odd to hear. My best guess is there was a shortage of cooks. While waiting I used a fairly nasty looking bathroom with toilet that didn’t flush.

The food itself was rather typical of this type of restaurant. The mozzarella sticks were initially delivered without marinara sauce, and my Parmesan shrimp pasta was comically served before the breadsticks was ready. My coworker was unable to order the rib combo he wanted because they had run out. Unfortunate experience.

I have already order twice and the two times was for pick up every time I have come here i always had to wait more than the time that the app told me it would be ready the extra time was about 20 minutes and it wasn't busy at all. I'm not happy with food portions the food is a little tasty but is not enough food for the price that they are charging this is mine and my brother's order, my brother ordered tender with 2 sides fries and loaded fries, I order triple play with fries and loaded fries. I find the tenders and fries to half of what it should have been. I don't think I will ever order here again.

This visit was average for us the food quality could have been more better I ordered the Philly Cheese Steak which was disappointing very little cheese on steak um like sandwich the only thing that saved our dinner was  the salad bar as the bar 🍸 drinks was not legendary as advertised .
Horrible 6 people in the entire dining room took over an hour to get out food. Manager blamed first day waitress. So she got a 30% tip and the manger got the heat from us.

First off I want to say I do happen to love Bojangles. It’s about the only fast food I eat, and only enjoy it when I’m down Maryland seeing family.

But this is by far the most disgustingly dirty restaurant I’ve ever been in. First thing in the morning 10am and the floor is sticky, and the bathrooms are in such horrible condition, they should be closed to the public.

This place should seriously be shut down for health concerns.

Left and would not eat food or recommend anything from this establishment at this time.

This was a classic down south restaurant that moved up north however the southern cooking style was not brought here . The sides were just ok and the chicken was very upsetting to me . I may return to give them another chance to get it right .

This place was really unhygienic. The floor in front of the counter was sticky. The soda fountain counter was extremely wet. There was no paper napkins. Half the tables were unclean and there is only one trash can in the whole dine-in area. It seems their drive thru was slam on a Sunday but that's really no excuse. I had the spicy chicken sandwich and there was so much mayo it was on the bun and wrapper. The family size fried chicken were good though. Won't be coming back to this one.

My understanding is that new owners have taken over, not Americans so the food has changed dramatically. In other words it is nasty. The CAJUN taste that were there is gone completely. Popeye is a CAJUN style restaurant, so in my opinion and my taste buds horrible. If all locations change the ingredients like this one, it won't be CAJUN anymore. I will not go back 😒 😤 there. Nasty, nasty, nasty....

Worse Bojangles experience ever! They didn’t have chicken breast, thighs, supremes, French fries, Mac and cheese, or honey mustard. I did get chicken tenders, but I couldn’t eat them because they were horrible and clearly not a real Bojangles item. The floors were filthy and the staff was unprofessional. One cook even had on a big red head bonnet that you would wear to bed. They even stopped taking orders from the drive through window. Poor management. I lived in Charlotte, NC for 20 years and know what real Bojangles tastes like. This is not it! Shape up or shut down!

This is by far the best location to dine in at. I sat in the bar area at a booth. Q the bar tender was the best, he was running the whole area I am really impressed my order was correct my food was perfect and the Atmosphere was calm. Of course let me not leave out the other staff. They were very supportive to my experience. I am full, relaxed and Happy Thank you Q for exceptional service. 😌🍰💅💯🧞‍♀️

Not even spoken to by when I approached the hosts stand, waiting 17 minutes for a waitress to come (after my partner asked for our server), having to share silverware with my family because they don't have any clean silverware, being served butts of lettuce in the salad, given mushy broccoli, dirty booths. The team is rude and the manager walks around ignoring the dirty floors and tables. ITS A COVID WORLD PUT SOAP IN THE BATHROOM 🚻 LETS NOT FORGET THE MOLDY FOOD MY CHILD WAS SERVED. I asked for a manager that never came.

Our food came quick and it was sooooo good! But the best part was the service! Our server was Shelby! He was very attentive. He offered me several alternatives to accommodate my dietary restrictions. Easily the best server i’ve had here.

My wife and I went to this location to enjoy a nice dinner, and had the “quickest dining experience ever” (quoting my wife).  While the customer service encounters with the staff was very pleasant, the service was way too rushed!  We ordered one beer, two appetizers, two entrees including two porterhouse steaks which were described by our waiter as “marbled.”  The soups and salads came first, followed by the beer and tea.  Not more than two minutes later the appetizers came with the bread. Keep in mind this a table for two, so now we had to put our beverage glasses on the bread plates for space because there was now NONE! The appetizers were way overpriced and the blooming onion was burnt as well, but we kept it all the same.  The wings were not as advertised, as they were super small, and at $15.89 a plate for 10 wings, that was crazy, but still we kept them.  Less then 5 minutes later here came the steaks, as with everything else brought by different staff members (never once by our waiter until the very end, keep reading) so they had no clue which steak was who’s.  The “marbled” steaks were both literally 1/2 fat and gristle, and the medium (I guess medium because again our waiter was not present to tell which one was which) steak was burnt on the outside.  We would have complained but the waiter, who after asking him several times for extra sauce for the burnt blooming onion, finally came with to go containers which we had not even asked for yet instead???? We ordered a desert to go since we felt like our presence or business was not appreciated.  We have always had excellent experiences overall with Outback in the past but this was by far the least favorable dining experience so far this year, and we will not recommend any member of the local community to expect anything more than this if they decide to spend over $135.00 on dinner with their family or friends.
Lunchtime & they weren't crowded. Wings came out hot & fresh. Tried the Chicken Ceaser salad. Service from the Bartender was excellent!

So I’m not vegan but I’m lactose intolerant and I thoroughly enjoyed everything I ate. The chicken filet tasted like chicken. The mac and cheese was creamy, seasoned, and didn’t have the weird after taste of other dairy free cheeses. The cheesecake was sweet and creamy and I was impressed. It’s definitely a takeout spot so expect to get your food and leave or enjoy it in the car because there’s no where to sit. Other than that the food is bomb!
Absolutely delicious. Flavors and textures were all on point. Lots of variety to choose from. Many veggie options. Great people and great pricing too!! 10/10 highly recommended.

Delicious 😋.! I really like the Strawberry seamoss gel. It has wild-crafted seamoss, strawberries, filtered water, and Agave. Its sweet tasting! I tried the chicken Tenders, Mac n cheese ( hemp and pea mix), and greens. I wasn't a huge fan of the flavor of the greens but the Mac n cheese was a hit! The young lady who helped me was super informative all the way to letting me know which dishes didn't have soy.  Will definitely be returning!!!

I love supporting an awesome Black-owned business such as ELife 🌱and with them being in business 27+ years you know they are doing a few things right!

Their pumpkin bread is 💣 and so delectable (even as a food demonstration when I had it!)

They offer so much as a restaurant, pop-up shop for black-owned businesses on weekends, perform food demos, host speaker events, and more 🎆.

Being a Sierra Club member we try to branch out and partner with organizations whenever possible. I recently went to the event with a food demo by Elife and a speaker talk by Sierra Club MA staff. It was epic!

I love the food I bought there recently, the jambalaya, cashew mac n cheese, and chickpeas 😍. Their paper menus they post are the current menus/food items they have (not sure if for all the restaurants, but it is for the Capitol Heights location.) Their black board standing menu at the front there is outdated.

Next time I go, I want to check out more of the salad bar 👀. Cheers!

If you are looking for a reason to eat here, I hope this review gives you that reason. The best vegan “soul”food I have ever had! You can also warm it up the next day and it’s still delicious. That gives them 5 ⭐️ in my book! I ordered Curry chicken, original Mac & cheese, and collard greens.

I went to the Largo location and was so looking forward to the smokehouse BBQ bacon grilled chicken sandwich. I waited in line for 15+ minutes. Had my order taken by a less than enthusiastic person. Waited some more to get my food. Then went back home to enjoy it. The disappointment I had when I opened the box. NO BACON. NO BBQ SAUCE. Just a plane grilled chicken sandwich. Check your food before you pull off. Especially if you’re just grabbing food on the go. I’ll just get a sandwich from Fridays next time.

If I could give zero stars, I absolutely would. I order at this location at least 2x/week and EVERY single time it’s an ordeal. Curbside and carry out takes 30-45 mins minimum…just for your order to be wrong. And my order is ALWAYS wrong-it’s the one thing I can count on. I order a cookie, I get Mac n cheese or a brownie, or just no cookie at all more often than not. I order a chicken biscuit (w/egg no cheese), I get biscuit with egg, cheese, and no chicken. I order a whole meal, not one sauce in sight. The worst part about it is the attitude they give you when point out that your $20 order is incorrect. And it’s not the kids either, it’s adults and/or management! At this point, I’d rather walk to the Bowie location because the “my pleasure” not my pleasure’n at this location.

The food is always on point at Chick-fil-A. The staff is very attentive helpful and friendly. The only thing that needs to be adjusted is the safety yellow poles that divides the two drive-thru lane in the parking lot. It’s unsafe for the customer driving and trying to make a safe left turn near the parking lot curb without driving over the curb. Can someone fixes this safety hazard by making the turning lane wide enough to turn.

Chick-fil-a is always good. My fries were nice and hot. My Frosted lemonade hit the spot on a nice warm day. There are healthier options there also. For instance I got a grilled chicken sandwich on wheat bread and we were able to get a fruit cup for our 1 year old. Good food on the go!

I have been in line forever. Frankly, this is the only time I’ve had a beef with paying for my food before getting to the window. The line took so long that I would have happily left if I didn’t already pay. I have not gotten my food yet but I hope it’s right. This was supposed to be a quick stop before school drop off… do better please!

Customer service in this area is awful. I ordered in ADVANCE for pick up at a specific time. When I get there to pick up my order they hadn’t even made it yet. They said that their policy is to confirm big orders prior to making it because it’s not paid for yet. Even though I can understand that, it was a terrible inconvenience and no one explained that to me when I placed the order. I think it’s important to be transparent to customers when because how else would we know what your business policies are? It’s so annoying and I won’t ever spend my money at an establishment who has such little regard for inconveniencing patrons.
fries are bland. i ordered honey lemon pepper and honey old bay wings & received plain wings. the wings also are weird.

With the  name, "America's Best Wings", what would one Expect- The BEST or at least CLOSE. The wings were not the best or even close. They were ROCK HARD. If you like HARD wings, this is THE place.

I had decided to eat in - Thankfully!!
I returned to the counter, and politely stated my concern about the HARD state of the wings and requested a replacement order. The young
man accepted my request and the ROCK HARD wings. Shortly, he returned with my replacement.  I thanked him and left - big MISTAKE. They at least as hard as the first order.

IF YOU LIKE 'ROCK HARD' WINGS - this is the place. If not, head for the hills - DO NOT ENTER. The
MEAT WAS, AT LEAST, AS HARD AS THE BONES.

I will spread the word and never return.

Consider this a word to the wise.

The wings here are great and this is always my family first choice when ordering out. The wings are fried to perfection and the presentation is amazing. However, I noticed whenever the owner or her family is in the kitchen cooking the food isn’t that great. I believe the owner is more focused on food time than the actual food. Some of the wings aren’t covered in the sauce and it looks like the food is just thrown in the container. I also realized that whenever she’s in the kitchen, my fries aren’t freshly cooked, I believe she is recooking fries. Keep the owner out the kitchen and this place would get 5 stars consistently!
I ordered the lemon pepper wings and i got fried chicken. The worst experience!

I wanted to like this place. The other customers were friendly and the place is convenient to Capital Region Hospital.

Fun place, with slow service, lack of attention to customers and mediocre food.

Small bar generally empty during the week and and it is a nice place to relax.

A steakhouse with the slogan that you can’t fake Formica. Or was it steak. No wood here. Didn’t do the steak. Dark inside, with the lights going on at 10 pm so people know to get ready to leave. Closing time is 11.

Came here at 9 pm and it was tough to get someone’s attention to order. Food (appetizer and side) took over 30 minutes to be served after ordering. Other patrons were friendly-staff was busy with the steak takeout business.

The best steak I’ve had in a long time! It was cooked to perfection and the crust was delicious. The sides and drinks were all delicious as well, especially the mac n cheese 🤤. Our server Chris was friendly and fast but dinner was not rushed. Will definitely return.

I have never experienced the level of just absolute ineptness and disregard for providing a worthy customer experience. I can disregard the fact my waiter was extremely high; however, that led to confusing information, drinks that had to be corrected such as giving us a long pour which was only 3/4 full and thinking the bs line that he was told to tell us would fly.  No saucer for apps or effort in timing with table delivery. But the person who ultimately responsible is the nonexistent Manager who was lacking in every part of their job on Saturday April 16, 2022. The food was okay but I really can't remember over the terrible experience. I will never eat here again and would not recommend this place to anyone. You have options with your money and where to spend it. Unless unrestrained ratchetness is your thing, eat somewhere where the service is at least as good as your meal. Did I mention how much I despise this place?

The area where the restaurant located in a newly development near the UMMC capital area in largo near FedEx field. The restaurant is very clean, very inviting and very friendly staff.
Our server Joshua was friendly, quick check on our table asking if we need anything. Food was very tasty and the steak was big portion and very good. We had a little issue, but the manager(sorry didn’t get her name right) resolved the issue in a very professional, and in a very polite manner. I thank her for her professionalism and respectfully resolving the issue quickly. She is Great 👍
I recommended this restaurant for everyone.

Overall dining experience was ok my server Keon check back with me often just a few things that didn't meet my expectations for the visit to MOD the restaurant was freezing cold very uncomfortable for eating and the French onion soup was very salty, the pilaf rice was very bland not like the pilaf rice I've tasted in other countries please work on restaurant comfort I felt as though I had to go get my sweater out of car for dining the steak was cooked perfectly good job.

The Rainbow Trout tremendous super good fish , phenomenal flavoring and seasoning
Crab cake sandwich was tremendous satisfying as well as flavorful with a nice herbs, crunchy frys and great coleslaw!!

As I entered the place the first thing that struck me was how clean it was, I mean G I clean emaciate. What threw me off after that was the supposed store manager in a Cameroon seafood shirt very loud and obnoxious. I actually witnessed him untaped a box for no reason and tape it back up I don't know what he was doing but it looked like not standard procedure. Then when he engaged me as we were talking he was eating and food was falling outta his mouth ( check the camera 10/06/22 some time between 3:30 and 6:45) I was the gentleman with the cane. The lady who took my order and the cook in the back of the house were awesome and she got my order correct. Now there was another incident with the gentleman,(the supposed manager) a woman walked in she was about 6feet beautiful African American Queen after she gave her order and she left, he made more then one unsuitable comments about her and the staff laughed. I will never spend another dollar in there for that fact because black dollars matter and every customer should be treated with some type of respect. The woman will never know but I do and it's an unforgivable thing to have  manager or whom ever he is to do that even if she never heard anything I did and quite possibly my family members or I could be next. NO I'LL SPEND MY DOLLARS ELSEWHERE AND ANYONE OF COLOR SHOULD TO. BESIDES THE FOOD I RECEIVED WAS BLAND WITH NO TASTE.

The worst place to order seafood, especially DONOT order online! I ordered 1 dozen of crab and soup, they are all arrived frozen! If these are not freshly made, why we spend hundreds$ on this？！ Stay away from this place!

🚫🚫DON'T WASTE YOUR MONEY!!This use to be a decent establishment, now it's just a trash facility! Ordered an ultimate and seafood platter and food was disgusting, unflavorful, tough and dry. Clearly the food was refried or reheated. The so called crabcake was stuck under the fish since it looked like a black bean veggie pattie and  was as hard as a hockey puck! Don't waste your money!!
The large male crabs 🦀 were 80.00 a dozen but it was worth it!!!!!! They tasted so good too.

It was good. Short staffed, but server Patrick was very busy, but he had a great attitude and was very sweet and took care of us. Blue margarita was awful. But, regular Margarita was good. Food was good, not great but good, coleslaw was awful. Food was hot each time it came out. $14.99 all you can eat, included, riblets, boneless chicken wings and shrimp, you get what you pay for. U have to keep asking for a serving of which dish you want. But overall, everything was good. Shrimp came out piping hot each time. First time here. But, I enjoyed myself with my husband. Started getting crowded around 4:30pm. Next time we'll get there around 12pm. We got there like 3:20p

One of my favorite lunch and dinner place to go for a eat sip and chill. I love there monthly drinks, appetizers....If y'all anything about da "Beez" Wonton Tacos and there Pepper Honey Boneless wings....you can't go wrong especially during Happy Hour time 😜 My favorite is the Oriental Salad I add Grilled Shrimp and Bacon to mines🤤

Picked up shrimp ceasar salad from the Applebee's in Largo, MD before going to the hair salon and a dead bug skeleton was in the salad. Places aren't clean so be careful. The best place to eat is in your own home.
Food was great, however, the place, including the tables were dirty and sticky. Need to do a better job in keeping the place clean

Food was not great. Pasta was overcooked (mushy) and steak was overcooked. Very very slow to get any service at all. Our server never came around to check on our meal or fill drinks. He was hanging out with other servers at the bar area. We had to go up to request our bill. Restaurant was very loud and rap music played the entire time we were there. We did not enjoy our experience at this Applebee's location at all.

name: Sardi's Pollo A La Brasa - Capitol Heights
vicinity: 8811 Hampton Mall Drive North, Capitol Heights

reviews.text: Chicken was tender and juicy. The sauce it came with is so creamy and has a touch of spiciness make the chicken taste so much better. Fried rice and fried yuca is ok. Empanadas was tasty as well. Overall affordable dinner meal for 2 people.

This was my first time going here and I like it. The three thousand 4.4 🌟 ratings in Google Maps made me curious if they were that good.  The chicken was juicy 😋 not charred or burnt and you had a choice of multiple sides not just French fries and yuca
I have been ordering the Greek Salad from Sardi’s as a meal form many years and it is always good. Today is was still good, however to salad is much smaller and cost more. It is now a side salad.

I got the pork and cheese pupusas, chicken and beef empanadas, and steak quesadilla. Pretty good overall. I wish I would have gotten more salsa for the quesadilla and a lime.The chicken empanada was bland and dry. That was disappointing given that the regular chicken is so juicy and flavorful. The steak empanadas were the opposite. Moist and tender shredded beef. Theyvforgot the dipping sauce so i cant aay if that would have made it better or not. Everything was hot! I even when I got home. Love that they made it to order. May just go back for more today! All total I spent $31 for 2 pupusas, 1 quesadillia (steak was extra), and 3 empanadas.

Food is good for carryout, but my favorite was the salmon skewers and roasted potatoes and they have disappeared from their menu. Check your bags too before leaving. For some reason, I am always missing a side that goes with a meal. Last time...fries that went with my salmon.

The girl taking the orders in the drive-thru has an attitude and doesn't know anything about customer service or how to greet people.
I asked when I picked up my food if my fries could be made over,
I was told to pull number one I did and the girl came right behind me with the same fries.
I know teenagers are cheap labor but sometimes they need to be trained better.

I waited in the drive thru several minutes. When my order was taken it was wrong. I said something but I thought the gentleman could not hear me. When I got to the window to pay I repeat that it was wrong. The girl wanted to take my money ignoring what I said. I finally had to drive off. I thought was it me. Or do they not care that I telling them my order is wrong. Awful customer service!!

McDonald's is, well. McDonald's and it is no longer a bargain to eat at. Of course, who doesn't love the fries, but I eat there very rarely because the food is not very healthy to put it mildly and not conducive towards longevity.
Condiments are important...they need to remember that french fries and chicken nuggets can't go without sauce and ketchup and ..so please provide it as a courtesy or ask if needed anything else?

The girls in the drive thru overnight shift are nasty and ugly asl.The Spanish girl at the first window acts as if somebody is forcing her ugly self to be there.The dusty black skinned one who looks like she drinks Newport Milkshakes and smoke weed all day tried to charge me $2 for a cup of ice knowing goodness well she was going to use that money to buy backwoods.The manager is outside with the cleaning crew sitting in their cars.The cleaning crew is trash they mop the bathrooms with old mop water which makes the smell in the bathroom even worst and it's filthy!!Juststraight ghetto and disappointing overall the entire night crew needs to be fired.
I literally went to Taco Bell and the nice pretty girl in the drive thru gave me a cup of ice no charge and with a smile..it sucks because this is the closest McDonald's to me and it's garbage
Attorney King is an excellent litigator.  She is brilliant in the courtroom and I would trust her with my life.  She is busy so consider yourself forutante if she can take your case.
Do not hire this woman!  She is a liar!

If I could give them no stars I would.. long story short someone took my card info in the drive through a decided to attempt a shopping spree. Everyone in the store acts like the manger is not available when u call the store .. I will be reporting to corporate. 7 on your side as well as an attorney.. The lack of communication it disgusting.. They need a more trustworthy staff ASAP

I ordered on line to pick up in drive thru thinking this would be faster. Well afteri drove up gave my name I was told to wait in a pick up space.  It took them 23minutes before I got out and went inside to only be told my order was given away to someone else. No apology no compensation no nothing......

Ordered a Number 2, food had the consistency of having been spit in -wet and slimey and clear in color, so it wasn't sauce. Hopefully, they have monitored cameras in there and an employee didn't actually spit in the food. Won't be back.

I attempted to grab what I thought would be a quick bite but was sadly mistaken. Instead, I received poor customer service, no food, and the runaround for my refund. The app is completely useless and only makes things worse.

I placed an online order that the store never received and when I started asking questions, they quickly got rude. I waited 15 minutes in one of their pick up parking spots and never received my food, and was only told I wouldn't be receiving my food when I pulled around the drive thru for the second time (this was after they initially told me I'd have to come inside despite placing an online order and selecting the option to pick it up via the drive thru).

I've received calls from the Store Manager and the District or Regional Manager (he was having phone issues so it was very hard to hear him) but neither of them have been helpful. One told me a refund was being processed from the corporate office and would be in my account after 7 business days. The other told me I'd have to dispute the charge with my bank. This is by far the worst fast food experience I've ever had, and we all know that's saying something.

I'm trying not to hold this incident against them forever but I'm not feeling great about eating at any Taco Bell again at the moment. I definitely won't be going back to the Largo, Maryland location anytime soon, if ever again.
Really clean Taco Bell nice staff etc. Quick service. Love this Taco Bell.
